    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hiberno-Norse refers specifically to the culure of Vikings linked to the Gaelic-speaking areas of Ireland. It was once used in a broader sense by scholars to characterize all Scandinavian culture in Gaelic-speaking areaw of North England as well as Ireland; and used in contrast to the related concept 'Anglo-Dane'.</Note_Text>
